#eNCA Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Labour Minister Thulas Nxesi says government has several programmes aimed at getting young people jobs. He's confident public employment programmes will address the unemployment crisis. READ: WATCH | Labour Minister speaks on prioritising workers' rights But he says the problem seems to be that the youth are unaware of such initiatives. "I must indicate what we're doing as [the] government in relation to the economic reconstruction and recovery plan, we're trying to address those issues of employment," Nxesi said. READ: Ramaphosa concerned about high levels of unemployment in SA "The public employment programme where we have created, through the president, more than 800,000 jobs. We're saying it's not going to be an event, it is going to be a long process to create jobs. "Let's allow for conversation, let's allow for the young people to make suggestions. "The fact that we're talking about small businesses and cut red tape. The fact that in the public service we have said now at the  entry level, the issue of experience must not be a requirement, we are trying to accommodate the young people."